Implemented Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js project.

Created:
- None (modified existing files only)

Modified:
- /app/layout.jsx - Added Analytics component import and placement
- /package.json - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- /package-lock.json - Updated lockfile with new dependency

Implementation Details:
1. Fetched the latest installation instructions from the official Vercel documentation at https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart
2. Identified that this project uses Next.js App Router (confirmed by the presence of app/layout.jsx)
3. Installed @vercel/analytics package using npm (the project's package manager)
4. Imported { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next' in the root layout file
5. Added <Analytics /> component within the <body> tag of the root layout, after the Providers component

The Analytics component will automatically track page views and other web vitals once deployed to Vercel. The implementation follows Vercel's official documentation for Next.js App Router projects.

Build Verification:
- Successfully ran `npm run build` with a placeholder GROQ_API_KEY environment variable
- Build completed successfully with all 144 routes compiled
- No new build errors or warnings introduced by the Analytics integration
- The Analytics component integrates seamlessly with the existing application structure

Next Steps:
- Deploy to Vercel to activate Web Analytics
- Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard for this project
- Monitor analytics data in the Vercel dashboard after deployment
